# SETUP — running on another machine (developer onboarding, {{PROJECT_SLUG}})

> Goal: after these steps your Claude Code works **identically** — run `/bootstrap` and go. Machine-specific
> is only the contents of your `.env` (gitignored) + CLI authorization. None of that lands in git. Project /
> role details — `CLAUDE.md`, `ai/rules/new-task-bootstrap.md`, `docs/taskctl.md`.

## 0. Prerequisites (what to install)
- **Node.js ≥ 20** and **git** — for `taskctl` (`node taskctl/cli.mjs`).
- **`claude` CLI** (Claude Code), authorized (`claude` → `/login`) — the taskctl planner shells into it.
- **`codex` CLI** (OpenAI Codex), authorized — the cross-model reviewer (`plan-review` / `review`).
- **Python 3** on PATH — for `ops/session-state.sh` / tracker queries.
- **bash** — on Windows use **Git Bash** for the `.sh` scripts.
